## Recommended Call Order

For every feature implementation or code generation task, call in this order:

```
1. list_collections(db)
   → Know exact collection names before writing @Document

2. find(db, collection, {}, limit=3, sort={created_at:-1})  ← for each relevant collection
   → Ground truth: real field names, types, nesting

3. list_indexes(db, collection)  ← for each relevant collection
   → Know which fields need @Indexed, @Indexed(unique), @CompoundIndex

4. count_documents(db, collection, {})  ← for each relevant collection
   → Decide on Pageable requirement

5. aggregate($lookup)  ← only if cross-collection relation suspected
   → Confirm the join works before writing service-layer join code

6. aggregate($group on string/enum fields)  ← for status/type/category fields
   → Get every real distinct value to define Java enum correctly
```

